{
  "diffMode": "text",
  "formatName": "Scalable Vector Graphics (SVG)",
  "version": "1.0",
  "extensions": [".svg", ".svgz"],
  "description": "SVG (Scalable Vector Graphics) — W3C XML-based 2D vector image format (1999, SVG 2.0 current). Starts with XML declaration '<?xml' or directly with '<svg'. Root element: <svg xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg' width='...' height='...' viewBox='...'>. Elements: <path d='M10,10 L90,90'> (Bezier curves, arcs), <circle>, <rect>, <ellipse>, <line>, <polyline>, <polygon>, <text> (with <tspan>), <image> (embedded raster), <g> (group), <defs> (reusable definitions), <use> (instance/clone), <symbol>, <marker>, <pattern>, <linearGradient>, <radialGradient>, <clipPath>, <mask>, <filter> (blur/shadow/compositing), <animate>, <animateTransform>, <animateMotion>, <set>. Embedded JavaScript: <script>. Embedded CSS: <style>. SVGZ: gzip-compressed SVG (magic 1F 8B). Security risk: SVG can contain JavaScript and external resource references — XSS risk when served as image/svg+xml and rendered by browsers. Inline SVG in HTML does not have the same sandboxing as <img src='.svg'>.",
  "category": "Images",
  "author": "WPFHexaEditor Team",
  "preferredEditor": "text-editor",
  "references": {
    "specifications": [
      "SVG 2.0 — W3C Candidate Recommendation (2018)",
      "SVG 1.1 Second Edition — W3C Recommendation (2011)",
      "CSS Shapes Module Level 1 — interaction with SVG"
    ],
    "WebLinks": [
      "https://www.w3.org/TR/SVG2/",
      "https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/SVG",
      "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/SVG"
    ]
  },
  "detection": {
    "signatures": [
      {
        "value": "3C737667",
        "offset": 0,
        "label": "<svg — SVG root element at offset 0",
        "weight": 0.9
      },
      {
        "value": "3C3F786D6C",
        "offset": 0,
        "label": "<?xml — SVG with XML declaration prefix",
        "weight": 0.4
      }
    ],
    "matchMode": "any",
    "MinimumScore": 0.3,
    "required": false,
    "Strength": "Medium",
    "EntropyHint": { "min": 3.5, "max": 5.5 },
    "validation": {
      "minFileSize": 5,
      "maxSignatureOffset": 0,
      "note": "SVG is XML text. May begin with '<?xml' (XML declaration) or directly with '<svg'. SVGZ files are gzip-compressed (magic 1F 8B). UTF-8 BOM (EF BB BF) may precede '<'. Inline SVG does not have the file-level '<svg' directly at offset 0."
    }
  },
  "variables": {
    "firstByte": 0,
    "svgTag": ""
  },
  "blocks": [
    {
      "type": "field",
      "name": "First Byte",
      "offset": 0,
      "length": 1,
      "color": "#FF6B6B",
      "opacity": 0.45,
      "description": "First byte of the SVG file at offset 0 (1 byte, uint8). Expected value 0x3C ('<') for standard SVG files — the opening angle bracket for either '<svg' or '<?xml'. SVGZ (compressed SVG) starts with 0x1F 0x8B (gzip magic) and must be decompressed before parsing as XML. UTF-8 BOM (0xEF 0xBB 0xBF) may precede the '<' in BOM-marked files. Non-'<' first bytes indicate either SVGZ, BOM, or non-SVG content.",
      "storeAs": "firstByte",
      "valueType": "uint8"
    },
    {
      "type": "field",
      "name": "SVG/XML Tag",
      "offset": 0,
      "length": 4,
      "color": "#4ECDC4",
      "opacity": 0.35,
      "description": "First 4 bytes of the SVG file (ASCII). Valid patterns: '<svg' (0x3C 0x73 0x76 0x67) = SVG without XML declaration; '<?xm' (0x3C 0x3F 0x78 0x6D) = XML declaration prefix '<?xml version=...'>'; '<!--' = SVG with XML comment before root; 0x1F 0x8B = SVGZ (gzip magic). Most modern SVG generators omit the XML declaration. The SVG root element must have xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg' namespace declaration.",
      "storeAs": "svgTag",
      "valueType": "ascii"
    },
    {
      "type": "metadata",
      "name": "First Byte",
      "variable": "firstByte",
      "description": "0x3C '<' for SVG/XML text; 0x1F for SVGZ (gzip)"
    },
    {
      "type": "metadata",
      "name": "SVG/XML Tag",
      "variable": "svgTag",
      "description": "'<svg' or '<?xm' — SVG file start identifier"
    }
  ],
  "assertions": [
    {
      "name": "SVG starts with XML tag",
      "expression": "firstByte == 0x3C",
      "severity": "warning",
      "message": "SVG file should start with '<' (0x3C) — may be SVGZ (gzip) or corrupted"
    },
    {
      "name": "SVG or XML tag present",
      "expression": "svgTag == '<svg' or svgTag == '<?xm'",
      "severity": "info",
      "message": "Expected SVG to start with '<svg' or '<?xml' — check for BOM or XML comment"
    }
  ],
  "navigation": {
    "bookmarks": [
      { "name": "SVG Root", "offset": 0, "icon": "\uE71B", "color": "#FF6B6B" }
    ]
  },
  "inspector": {
    "badge": "firstByte",
    "primaryField": "svgTag",
    "showQualityScore": true,
    "groups": [
      {
        "title": "SVG Header",
        "icon": "\uE71B",
        "fields": ["firstByte", "svgTag"]
      }
    ]
  },
  "exportTemplates": [
    {
      "name": "SVG Info (JSON)",
      "format": "json",
      "fields": ["firstByte", "svgTag"]
    },
    {
      "name": "SVG Header (Text)",
      "format": "text",
      "fields": ["svgTag"]
    }
  ],
  "forensic": {
    "category": "web-content",
    "riskLevel": "medium",
    "suspiciousPatterns": [
      "<script> elements in SVG may contain malicious JavaScript — XSS vector when served as image/svg+xml",
      "<use xlink:href='http://...'/> or <image href='http://...'/> loads external resources — SSRF risk",
      "<foreignObject> allows embedding HTML within SVG — potential XSS escalation",
      "SVG served as image/svg+xml with JavaScript executes in browser security context",
      "SVGZ gzip compression may hide malicious content from naive text scanners"
    ]
  },
  "aiHints": {
    "analysisContext": "SVG = XML with SVG namespace. Root <svg> attributes: xmlns (required), width/height (px/mm/etc or 100%), viewBox='minX minY width height', preserveAspectRatio. Path data: M(moveto) L(lineto) C(cubic bezier) Q(quadratic) A(arc) Z(close) — absolute uppercase, relative lowercase. Text: <text x y font-family font-size fill>. Gradients: <linearGradient id>/<radialGradient id> in <defs>, referenced via fill='url(#id)'. Filters: <filter id><feGaussianBlur/><feColorMatrix/></filter>. Security: scan for <script>, javascript: URLs in href/onclick, <use> with external href, data: URIs in image src, <animate> with malformed values. SVGZ: gzip magic 1F 8B at offset 0 — need gzip decompression before XML parse.",
    "suggestedInspections": [
      "Bytes 0-3: '<svg' or '<?xm' confirms SVG text format; 0x1F 0x8B = SVGZ gzip",
      "Scan for '<script' or 'javascript:' — XSS risk if SVG served as image/svg+xml",
      "Check xmlns attribute on <svg> — should be 'http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'",
      "Look for <image>, <use xlink:href>, or <feImage> pointing to external URLs"
    ]
  },
  "software": [
    "Adobe Illustrator (primary SVG authoring tool)",
    "Inkscape (open-source SVG editor)",
    "Figma (exports SVG from designs)",
    "Sketch (macOS SVG export)",
    "All modern web browsers (native SVG rendering)",
    "SVGO (SVG optimizer CLI)",
    "librsvg (GNOME SVG rendering library)"
  ],
  "formatRelationships": {
    "category": "Images",
    "extensions": [".svg", ".svgz"],
    "relatedFormats": ["PDF", "EPS"],
    "note": "SVG is the dominant vector graphics format for the web. PDF/EPS are used for print. AI (Adobe Illustrator) is SVG-based internally. SVGZ is gzip-compressed SVG — same content, smaller file size, but must be served with Content-Encoding: gzip. Lottie/BodyMovin uses JSON-encoded animation as an alternative for complex animations. CSS can style and animate SVG elements directly."
  },
  "MimeTypes": [
    "image/svg+xml",
    "image/svg+xml-compressed"
  ],
  "UseCases": [
    "Web icons and logos (scalable at any resolution without pixelation)",
    "Data visualization charts (D3.js, Chart.js SVG output)",
    "UI illustrations and animations (CSS/SMIL animation)",
    "Print-ready diagrams and technical drawings",
    "Favicon and app icon source for multi-resolution generation"
  ],
